feat(ui): TradePlanCard surfaces regime + validation history + management

Stock detail page is where paying users make go/no-go decisions. The card
was missing three blocks despite the backend already returning them:

  1. Market Regime tile — label / ADX / EMA200 slope so the trader knows
     why this setup is or isn't allowed today.
  2. Setup Historical Performance — validation.status badge plus
     win_rate / expectancy_R / profit_factor / sample_size. When the
     setup is "unvalidated" (insufficient sample), a note explains why
     this is research-only.
  3. Dynamic Stop Management — move-to-breakeven trigger, trailing-stop
     ATR multiple + current trail price, scale-out percentages, and
     max-hold timeout, all from plan.management.

Frontend types updated: TradePlanResponse gains regime / management /
validation / production_status fields matching the backend payload.

Homepage polish
- Hero CTAs now lead with "進入研究終端機" (`/terminal`) alongside the
  existing Scanner shortcut. Terminal is the actual differentiator now.
- Trust signals upgraded with verifiable claims:
    3,291  walk-forward evaluated signals
    TOP 100 symbols × 5 years OHLCV
    0      lookahead bias
    TWSE / TPEX public data only

Build: clean, 23 routes, no type errors.

